chat_messages.text:
 Oh, you want to **merge Module 1 and Module 2 outputs** before feeding into Module 3.

---

## **Merged Data Structure for Module 3 Input**

```json
{
  "conversation_id": "{{from_module1}}",
  "timestamp": "{{current_timestamp}}",

  "intent": "{{from_module1}}",
  "confidence": "{{from_module1}}",
  "is_followup_answer": "{{from_module1}}",

  "merged_data": {
    "client_name": "{{from_module2_partial_data}}",
    "project_type": "{{from_module2_partial_data}}",
    "budget": "{{from_module2_partial_data}}",
    "timeline": "{{from_module2_partial_data}}",
    "start_date": "{{from_module2_partial_data}}",
    "location": "{{from_module2_partial_data}}",
    "scope_description": "{{from_module2_partial_data}}",
    "special_requirements": "{{from_module2_partial_data}}"
  },

  "confidence_scores": {
    "{{from_module2}}"
  },

  "clarification_attempts": "{{from_sheets}}",
  "previous_state": "{{from_sheets}}",
  "awaiting_field": "{{from_sheets}}"
}
```

---

## **Make.com: Data Aggregator Step (Between Module 2 and Module 3)**

Add a **Set Multiple Variables** module in Make.com:

```
Set Variables:
├─ intent = {{module1.intent}}
├─ confidence = {{module1.confidence}}
├─ is_followup = {{module1.is_followup_answer}}
├─ merged_data = {{module2.partial_data}}
├─ confidence_scores = {{module2.confidence_scores}}
├─ clarification_attempts = {{sheets.clarification_attempts}}
├─ previous_state = {{sheets.state}}
└─ awaiting_field = {{sheets.awaiting_field}}

Then pass this bundle to Module 3
```

---

## **Simplified Module 3 Prompt Input**

```
INTENT: {{aggregated.intent}}
CONFIDENCE: {{aggregated.confidence}}
DATA: {{aggregated.merged_data}}
CONFIDENCE SCORES: {{aggregated.confidence_scores}}
CLARIFICATION_ATTEMPTS: {{aggregated.clarification_attempts}}
PREVIOUS_STATE: {{aggregated.previous_state}}
AWAITING_FIELD: {{aggregated.awaiting_field}}

[rest of module 3 prompt...]
```

---

Does this solve it? One clean bundle of data going into Module 3?
